ion {\n    pub start: usize,\n    pub end: usize,\n    pub author_id: String,\n    pub ts: u128,\n    // + new: pub message_id: Option<String>,\n}\n```\nThen `update_attributions` (`attribution_tracker.rs:550`) — the function that imara-diffs old→new content — needs the same treatment as `author_id`: preserved regions keep their old message_id; newly-stamped regions get the *current* message_id (which the caller passes in alongside `current_author`). Once that's done, `transform_attributions_to_final` carries message_id through rebase/squash for free, **using the same content-diff projection that already makes line numbers correct.**\n\n### 2. Carry `message_id` through `LineAttribution`\nFile: `attribution_tracker.rs:40-50`\n```rust\npub struct LineAttribution {\n    pub start_line: u32,\n    pub end_line: u32,\n    pub author_id: String,\n    pub overrode: Option<String>,\n    // + new: pub message_id: Option<String>,\n}\n```\n`attributions_to_line_attributions` (`attribution_tracker.rs:2003-2077`) currently picks one dominant author per line via an overlap sweep — it'd need to also pick a dominant message_id per line (either an extra sweep, or a small generalization of the existing one).\n\nThe struct-literal site at `rebase_authorship.rs:2610-2615` (the hunk-based shifter) needs `message_id: attr.message_id.clone()` added — one line. Otherwise the message_id silently drops on rebase paths that take that branch.\n\n### 3. Emit a parallel attestation\nFile: `virtual_attribution.rs:988-1076` (`to_authorship_log()`). The existing loop groups by `author_id`. We add a second loop grouping by `message_id` (skipping `None`) and emit it into a parallel collection — either a second `Vec<FileAttestation>` in `metadata.message_attestations`, or a second text block before/after the existing one.\n\n## Why this is the same logic — not a parallel implementation\n\nThe reason \"the existing rebase/squash logic\" works for the conversation hash is:\n- char-level attributions are