thetic_msg_resolver` on `VirtualAttributions`; populated in all three `from_*` methods; consumed in both `to_authorship_log` and `to_authorship_log_and_initial_working_log`.\n\n## Status\n\n- `cargo build` clean.\n- All 1320 lib tests pass (3 new message-attestation tests + 1317 prior).\n- The dev binary at `target/debug/git-ai` is rebuilt; it's the symlink target of `/Users/Andrew/.git-ai-local-dev/gitwrap/bin/git`, so the next `git commit` from your test repo will use the fixed code.\n\n## To verify on your end\n\nRe-run the same test scenario in `git-ai-testing/` (M1 edits 1-4, human edits 4 + 6, M2 edits 2/3/7, human edits 7). The message attestation should now show:\n\n```\nmessage_attestation_testing.txt\n  fe867a2f-…  1\n  272ca353-…  2-3\n```\n\n(M1 claims line 1; M2 claims 2-3; lines 4 and 6-7 dropped because a human was the last editor — Q2=a.)\n\nIf line 1 is still missing or any id is wrong, send me the new `.git/ai/working_logs/<sha>/checkpoints.jsonl` from that run and I'll trace further.",
